  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Haiti Trauma Awareness and Resilience Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Leaders (pastors, teachers, doctors); Those handicapped during earthquake; Those who have lost family members; Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MCC has joined with Eastern Mennonite University (Center for Justice and Peacebuilding) to build resilient individuals and healthy communities by addressing trauma caused by the 2010 earthquake as well as historical social traumas experienced by Haitians. The Trauma Awareness and Resilience staff, in collaboration with Haitian advisors and local church and communities leaders, will design a program appropriate to Haiti&#x2019;s context so that Haitians can help each other deal with the trauma they have experienced. Partner organizations and individuals will obtain resources to deliver training in trauma awareness, resilience and healing to a wide cross section of Haitian society. The program will listen and include the Haitian community in all aspects of the program such as assessment, program development, and program delivery, while building capacity of individual staff, advisors and partner organizations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Trauma healing workshops have been conducted in Haiti; with 200 participants in year one and 544 participants trained in year two. Two level II trainings have been held for 43 trainers. 52 participants who have participated in the workshops have gone to their communities and provided similar trainings in their home and organizations. Presentations have also been conducted for approximately 1,141 church members and for 343 IDPs across 7 tent camps.</narrative>
  </description>
